On 2-May-05, at 4:06 PM, Greg Potts wrote:

> If you're going to go FI you are better off staying with L-jetronic so 
> that you don't have to reinvent everything. It will also be a lot 
> easier to get advice about. Get the injection from a 1975 federal bus 
> or a 1974 California model, as they had 1.8L engines as well and this 
> is closest available match to your engine's 1.7L dislplacement. If 
> possible, get the fuel tank firewall panel and the air cleaner bracket 
> from an FI donor bus. This will give you the bracket to hang the decel 
> valve from.
